Aesculus indica

   [2857.jpg]
    Authority   Griff.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Sapindales:Hippocastanaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names Indian chestnut, castanheiro da India
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 2857

   Notes
   SOURCES
   Joshi H 1980a pp 258-261 [TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, DRA, PH, LIG]
   KILLING T
   Below -8Â°C.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial deciduous tree. In India the new leaves appear in April, the
   flowers appear from April to June, fruits ripen in October-November,
   and the leaves fall in October-December.
   COMMON NAMES
   Indian horse chestnut, Pangar, Gugu, Kankar, Bankhor, Hane, Han, Kakra,
   Kishing, Hannudun, Gun, Khanor, Bankhor, Gu, Pu.
   FURTHER INF
   Indian horse chestnut can reach a height of 30-36 m. It can be found
   from Indus to Nepal at elevations from 1200-3000 m. In India, it is
   adapted to a relative humidity in January from 60-80% and in July from
   60-90%.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
